08/12/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Seven soldiers were killed and four others were wounded on Monday (December 7th) by gunmen who opened fire on a gendarmerie team near the village of Sazak in the northern Tokat province. Authorities suspect the attackers were Kurdish or leftist rebels, as both are believed to be active in the area. (Hurriyet, AP, BBC - 07/12/09)
